      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation execution checklist with independent review; boundary condition application verified by second analyst.",
      "rationale": "Execution checklist exists and is followed. Independent second-analyst review of boundary condition files was performed for 3 of 5 operating points only; time constraints prevented full coverage. Achieved level 2 against required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection justified by sensitivity study; hemolysis power-law constants derived from species-appropriate RBC fragility data; non-Newtonian viscosity model evaluated.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega selected based on prior FDA pump literature; sensitivity to turbulence model not re-evaluated after the January 2026 model revision that altered turbulence model constants. Hemolysis constants from Giersiepen et al. (1990) — species match is acceptable but constants are not re-fit to modern RBC data. Non-Newtonian effects neglected. Achieved level 3 against required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model inputs (geometry tolerances, fluid properties, operating conditions) characterized with probability distributions; Monte Carlo UQ propagates input uncertainty to hemolysis index.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ performed with 500 samples over inlet flow rate, rotational speed, and fluid viscosity distributions. Geometry manufacturing tolerances not included in UQ due to absence of as-built metrology data for the post-revision impeller geometry. Blood analog viscosity distribution sourced from the 2025-Q3 material properties dataset, which predates the January 2026 model revision. Achieved level 3 against required level 5.",
